Kayode Oyero The Presidential Task Force on COVID-19 has maintained that the ban on interstate movement remained in place, urging security agencies to tighten their enforcement level. PTF Chairman and Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Boss Mustapha, made this known during a briefing on Monday. While giving an update, Mustapha said, “We also appeal to the security agents to enforce the ban on interstate travel very strictly.” The SGF appealed to the public to comply with the laid-down protocols while also warning against public gatherings. “Gatherings are still not open of any form, we must avoid it either driving, shows, rallies of whatever categories, be responsible. Lifted restriction does not mean carelessness and that life is normal. Yes, there is a normal – but it is a new normal,” he added.